	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				HE IS FINALLY MINE!  Last night I had about an hour to play so I decided I'd run around Cauldron for a bit.  I got tired of running so I started training the goblin camp to the NPCs to let them kill the gobs for me.  I'd pick up anything else I found along the way for good measure.<BR>
<BR>
Well at some point, I went to pull the camp and it was filled with 4 tidal lords.  Coincidence?  Probably.  I pulled them to the NPCs and it took them awhile to kill them all off.  Meanwhile after two had gone down, I fired up tracking and I was couldn't believe my eyes.. BILGE FARFATHOM!!!  So I waited 5 seconds until the NPCs were working on the last of the goblins and then tracked him to underwater close to the shore.  <BR>
<BR>
Did he spawn right there?  I have no idea.  Does he stop there or was he stuck?  Again, no idea.  <BR>
<BR>
I immediately homed in on him and got attacked.  Once I got him to chase me out of the water instead of shooting his bow, I got him snared.  I assure you it's not possible for him to be any higher than Level 35 at most.  The Level 35 dwarves of BB were blue at 47, green at 48.  Bilge was green at 48 so he cannot be higher than 35.  As you might have guessed, he was easy for a 48 Druid, took me from about 80% mana to about 30%.  <BR>
<BR>
No totem, but I'll settle for the belt.  Just wanted to finish off my involvement on this thread.  I hope this information helps others find him.  Poor clerics have almost no chance at least not based on the fact that I caught Bilge underwater. :(
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
